<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Hasher</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-14 02:17:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Players who sell this to players for 45pp and spend more than 1 minute auctioning it are stupid. It amazes me how often people spend a great deal of time to sell something for either less than or about the same as a merchant will pay you. My wood-elf ranger with just + 18 CHA from a crude stein (20pp) and the + 3 Cha necklace (10pp??) can sell the CLS for more than 44pp in Kelethin to any old merchant, yet I have seen people selling it for less than 45pp! If you don't mind having this item in a bank slot for a while then you should hold out for 60pp and you will eventually get it. If you don't want to wait then get your CHA buff items on and sell it at a merchant with whom you have good faction.</font></td></tr></table>
