<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Virtutis</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-10 11:54:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>CLS is, at best, a comprimise weapon for those of us stuck between weapons.  As a 16th level Paladin, I've reached a point where my mino axe, while doing enough damage, is just too slow and, of course, is useless against magic-only critters.  I've got a crested Mistmoor for bashing purposes and love it to pieces but the CLS just doesn't hit hard enough (especially since I shall never dual wield and don't get double attack until 20) against the Mammoth Calves, Gnoll Commanders and other beasties you've got to take on to get above level 20.  That said, it's readily available without hagging, hits quickly, and, oh yes, will teach IBS's a lesson in manners.<BR>
<BR>
All the best,<BR>
<BR>
Virtutis Gasconard<BR>
Paladin Knower of the 16th Virtue<BR>
Servant of Rodcet Nife<BR>
Prexus<BR>
<BR>
P.S. For the earlier questioner, the CLS has no magic PROC. It is simply "magic" and can, therefore, strike magic-only MOBs.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
